0aluminum%20is%20about%204%2C478%C2%B0F.%20She%20also%20notes%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsun-surface-photos-video-reveal-boiling-plasma-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20surface%20of%20the%20sun%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bblisteringly%20hot%26quot%3B%2010%2C340%C2%B0F%2C%20according%20to%20NASA%20%E2%80%94%20far%20below%20the%20company's%20maximum%20manufacturing%20temperature.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20SharkNinja%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20a%20comment%2C%20there%20is%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20its%20claims%20are%20physically%20possible.%20Even%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20the%20Danish%20cookware%20company%20Scanpan%20was%20coating%20its%20pans%20by%20heating%20up%20a%20mixture%20of%20ceramic%20and%20titanium%20to%2030%2C000%C2%B0F%20and%20firing%20the%20resulting%20plasma%20particles%20at%20the%20surface%20of%20its%20pans%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Flifestyle%2Ffood%2F2002%2F04%2F03%2Fstuck-on-nonstick%2F48f31790-e136-4a85-bce1-7c7ae23b580b%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBrown's%20legal%20counsel%20told%20Insider%20that%20it's%20too%20early%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20case%2C%20but%20the%20lawsuit%20has%20gained%20the%20attention%20of%20some%20experts%20on%20advertising%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGonzalo%20E.%20Mon%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Kelley%20Drye%20%26amp%3B%20Warren%20LLP%20who%20is%20not%20directly%20involved%20in%20the%20case%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20SharkNinja%20case%20initially%20caught%20his%20eye%20because%20the%20language%20of%20the%20complaint%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20over%20the%20top%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20thought%20it%20might%20make%20for%20a%20catchy%20blog%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kelleydrye.com%2Fviewpoints%2Fblogs%2Fad-law-access%2Fsharkninja-faces-heat-over-temperature-and-non-stick-claims%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20his%20post%2C%20Mon%20references%20a%202021%20case%2C%20also%20cited%20by%20Brown%2C%20in%20which%20the%20National%20Advertising%20Division%20reviewed%20SharkNinja's%20claims.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20NAD%20didn't%20actually%20dispute%20SharkNinja's%20temperature%20claims%2C%20but%20they%20determined%20that%20SharkNinja%20didn't%20provide%20enough%20evidence%20that%20its%20cookware%20exhibited%20more%20resistance%20to%20%26quot%3Bsticking%2C%20chipping%2C%20and%20flaking%26quot%3B%20than%20traditional%20nonstick%20pans%2C%20Mon%20noted%20in%20his%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20was%20interesting%20in%20this%20case%20is%20that%20they%20only%20tested%20one%20food.%20They%20tested%20scrambled%20eggs%2C%26quot%3B%20Mon%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BClearly%2C%20one%20food%20was%20not%20enough%20for%20NAD%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20say%20how%20many%20the%20company%20had%20to%20test.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Brown's%20case%20unfolds%2C%20Mon%20said%20he's%20waiting%20to%20see%20whether%20SharkNinja%20will%20present%20evidence%20on%20additional%20foods%20they've%20tested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20lawsuit%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20certified%20as%20a%20class-action%2C%20Brown%20claims%20there%20are%20thousands%20of%20purchasers%20who%20have%20been%20hurt%20by%20the%20company's%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsharkninja-sued-pans-made-with-temperature-hotter-than-sun-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698520628000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653cfd48356802a56be6bffe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsharkninja-sued-pans-made-with-temperature-hotter-than-sun-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20is%20a