iting%20in%20the%20Financial%20Times%2C%20former%20US%20diplomat%20Richard%20Haas%20urged%20Israel%20to%20rethink%20its%20Gaza%20war.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHaas%20served%20in%20the%20Bush%20administration%20during%20the%20lead%20up%20to%20the%202003%20invasion%20of%20Iraq.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHaas%20said%20Israel%20has%20the%20right%20to%20attack%20Hamas%20but%20destroying%20the%20group%20is%20%26quot%3Bunlikely%20to%20prove%20doable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20diplomat%20who%20served%20in%20the%20Bush%20administration%20and%20as%20president%20of%20the%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%20has%20joined%20a%20chorus%20of%20elite%20voices%20urging%20Israel%20against%20launching%20a%20full-scale%20ground%20invasion%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWriting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F779d082a-efdc-4ae4-86b4-aaebec88f810%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Richard%20Haas%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20an%20advisor%20to%20former%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Colin%20Powell%20from%202001%20to%202003%2C%20and%20then%20as%20the%20United%20States'%20special%20envoy%20to%20Northern%20Ireland%2C%20argued%20that%20Israel%20has%20a%20right%20to%20go%20after%20Hamas%20following%20its%20Oct.%207%20massacre%20of%20more%20than%201%2C400%20people.%20Indeed%2C%20he%20said%20that%20it%20meets%20the%20criteria%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Bobligatory%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20right%20to%20go%20after%20Hamas%20does%20not%20mean%20all%20means%20of%20doing%20so%20are%20equally%20desirable%2C%20Haas%20said%2C%20cautioning%20Israel%20against%20a%20maximalist%20goal%20of%20completely%20eliminating%20the%20group.%20Hass'%20warning%20comes%20after%20US%20officials%20have%20also%20begun%20urging%20the%20Israeli%20government%20to%20rethink%20a%20ground%20war%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2F10%2F27%2Fus-urging-israel-