223957%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldie%20poses%20for%20a%20portrait%2C%20in%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20near%20the%20town%20of%20Orikhiv%2C%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%2C%20on%20October%201%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EROMAN%20PILIPEY%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine's%20soldiers%20are%20%26quot%3Bsteely%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdetermined%26quot%3B%20but%20also%20experiencing%20burnout%2C%20an%20expert%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMelinda%20Haring%2C%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%2C%20just%20returned%20from%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20frontlines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20stories%20of%20divorce%20and%20of%20family%20separation%20and%20also%20depression%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20than%20600%20days%20now%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20withstood%20a%20full-scale%20invasion%20that%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvladimir-putin-russian-forces-could-take-kyiv-ukraine-two-days-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupposed%20to%20lose%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20about%2048%20hours.%20But%20that%20defense%20is%20taking%20its%20toll%20on%20frontline%20soldiers%20who%20feel%20they%20are%20bearing%20a%20heavy%20burden%20that%20is%20not%20shared%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20society%2C%20Melinda%20Haring%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20told%20Insider%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzaporizhzhia-ukraine-front-line-life-expert-visit-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20interview%20following%20a%20recent%20trip%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20flinty%20and%20steely%20and%20determined%2C%26quot%3B%20Haring%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20think%20tank%2C%20said%20of%20the%20soldiers%20she%20spoke%20to%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%2C%20a%20southeastern%20region%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20which%20is%20occupied%20by%20Russian%20troops.%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20you%20talk%20to%20them%20for%20more%20than%20five%20minutes%2C%20they'll%20tell%20you%20that%20there's%20frustration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20issue%20is%20time%2C%20or%20the%20lack%20thereof%2C%20away%20from%20the%20battlefield.%20Soldiers%20only%20get%2030%20days%20off%20each%20year%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20can%20only%20take%20up%20to%2010%20days%20off%20at%20a%20time.%20That%20means%2C%20since%20February%202022%2C%20most%20%26quot%3Bhaven't%20seen%20much%20of%20their%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20Haring%20said.%20And%20that%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20a%20source%20of%20tension.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20them%20feel%20like%20there's%20not%20a%20whole-of-society%20effort%20behind%20them.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20are%20in%20Kyiv%20posing%20for%20selfies%20and%20eating%20in%20restaurants%2C%20while%20a%20small%20segment%20of%20Ukrainian%20society%20is%20the%20one%20that's%20sticking%20its%20neck%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Haring%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20common%20feeling.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20stories%20of%20divorce%2C%20and%20of%20family%20separation%2C%20and%20also%20depression.%20And%20a%20lot%20of%20PTSD.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20feeling%20that%20Ukraine's%20allies%20are%20asking%20the%20country's%20armed%20forces%20to%20fight%20a%20war%20in%20a%20way%20that%20they%20never%20would%20ask%20their%20own%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20talking%20to%20soldiers%20on%20the%20frontlines%2C%20they%20did%20say%2C%20overall%2C%20the%20mood%20was%20one%20of%20determination%2C%20but%20also%3A%20'We%20can't%20keep%20doing%20this%20without%20air%20power.%20You%20can't%20ask%20us%20to%20do%20this.%20You%20can't%20ask%20us%20to%20fight%20in%20a%20way%20you%20wouldn't%20fight%20yourself.'%20They're%20very%20eager%20to%20have%20air%20cover%2C%26quot%3B%20Haring%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20suffered%20staggering%20losses%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20even%20as%20it%20largely%20enjoys%20air%20supremacy.%20In%20August%2C%20US%20officials%20said%20as%20many%20as%20120%2C000%20Russian%20troops%20had%20been%20killed%20and%20up%20to%20180%2C000%20wounded%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F18%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fukraine-russia-war-casualties.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20Ukraine%20has%20also%20lost%20many%20people%3A%20about%2070%2C000%20soldiers%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20the%20officials%20said%2C%20and%20as%20many%20as%20120%2C000%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20toll%2C%20Haring%20said%2C%20is%20felt%20on%20the%20frontlines.%20Those%20who%20have%20survived%20the%20fighting%20thus%20far%20are%20eager%20for%20it%20to%20end%20%E2%80%94%20albeit%20not%20at%20any%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20that%20I%20was%20surprised%20with%20is%20we%20have%20these%20intricate%20debates%20about%2C%20'What%20is%20victory%3F'%26quot%3B%20Haring%20said.%20'But%20when%20you%20go%20and%20talk%20to%20soldiers%2C%20they%20just%20want%20to%20go%20home.%20They%20want%20peace%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20go%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20normal%20human%20reaction%20to%20a%20year-and-a-half%20of%20bloodshed.%20But%20it%20should%20not%20be%20read%20as%20a%20desire%20for%20peace%20on%20Russia's%20terms%2C%20Haring%20stressed.%20After%20all%20the%20alleged%20Russian%20war%20crimes%20in%20cities%20such%20as%20Bucha%20and%20Mariupol%2C%20most%20Ukrainians%20feel%20they%20%26quot%3Bhave%20given%20too%20much%26quot%3B%20to%20settle%20for%20anything%20less%20than%20fully%20expelling%20the%20enemy%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20freezing%20the%20conflict%20with%20a%20cease-fire%20may%20have%20some%20attraction%2C%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20is%20not%20interested%20in%20good-faith%20negotiations%2C%20Haring%20