e%20or%20the%20other%2C%20and%20by%20constantly%20expanding%20settlements%2C%20Israel%20showed%20that%20it%20prefers%20land%20to%20peace.%E2%80%99%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Israel%20by%20its%20actions%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20is%20not%20interested%20in%20having%20a%20Palestinian%20partner%20for%20peace%20because%20it%20wants%20to%20maintain%20its%20control%20over%20the%20territory.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Israel%20refuses%20to%20accept%20Hamas%20as%20a%20negotiating%20partner.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20position%20is%20that%20Hamas%20is%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20%E2%80%93%20pure%20and%20simple.%20It%20will%20never%20negotiate%20with%20it.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20policy%20has%20been%20to%20let%20Hamas%20rule%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20but%20to%20contain%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20and%20this%20policy%20collapsed%2C%20because%20Gaza%20could%20not%20be%20contained.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98What%20Israel%20refuses%20to%20do%20is%20to%20accept%20that%20Hamas%20represents%20a%20serious%20body%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20and%20that%20you%20cannot%20reach%20any%20peace%20agreement%20with%20the%20Palestinians%20that%20excludes%20Hamas.%20So%2C%20the%20sensible%20thing%20for%20Israel%20to%20do%20and%20the%20other%20European%20powers%20to%20do%20is%20to%20recognise%20Hamas%20and%20to%20negotiate%20with%20Hamas%20for%20a%20political%20settlement%20of%20the%20conflict.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98This%20is%20a%20political%20conflict%20between%20the%20two%20sides%2C%20but%20Israel%20only%20uses%20brute%20military%20force%20to%20suppress%20the%20Palestinians%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20nothing%20but%20brute%20military%20force.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98What%20we%20are%20witnessing%20today%2C%20day%20after%20day%2C%20in%20Gaza%20is%20Israel%20moving%20towards%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20the%20population%20and%20genocide.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98The%20West%20also%20bears%20a%20part%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20present%20and%20past%2C%20because%20of%20its%20massive%20support%20for%20Israel%2C%20its%20supply%20of%20arms%20to%20Israel%2C%20and%20its%20diplomatic%20protection%20of%20Israel.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98My%20duty%20as%20a%20public%20intellectual%2C%20and%20as%20a%20student%20of%20this%20conflict%2C%20is%20to%20give%20the%20public%E2%80%A6%20an%20account%20of%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20which%20is%20as%20truthful%20as%20possible%2C%20as%20honest%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20as%20fair-minded%20as%20possible.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelow%20is%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20full%20interview%2C%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style%2C%20clarity%20and%20syntax.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E.%20As%20we%20approach%20the%20end%20of%20three%20weeks%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%2C%20we%20ask%2C%20do%20we%20really%20know%20and%20understand%20the%20history%20of%20the%20relationship%20and%20struggle%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%3F%20There%20are%20many%20who%20believe%20that%20until%20history%20is%20properly%20understood%2C%20you%20cannot%20really%20understand%20why%20%5Bthe%20incident%20on%5D%20October%207%20happened.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoining%20me%20now%20from%20Oxford%20is%20someone%20who%20is%20going%20to%20explain%20to%20us%20the%20history%20as%20he%20sees%20it.%20Professor%20Avi%20Shlaim%20is%20an%20Emeritus%20Professor%20of%20International%20Relations%20at%20Oxford%20University%20and%20the%20author%20of%20seminal%20books%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ci%3EIsrael%20and%20Palestine%3A%20Reappraisals%2C%20Revisions%20Refutations%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Iron%20Wall%3A%20Israel%20and%20the%20Arab%20World.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%2C%20in%20your%20books%20and%20essays%2C%20you%20trace%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%20to%20the%2019th%20century%20Zionist%20movement%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20create%20an%20independent%20Jewish%20state%20in%20Palestine%2C%20in%20which%20Jews%20would%20constitute%20the%20majority.%20But%20you%20say%20the%20principal%20problem%20with%20this%20project%20was%20that%20Palestine%20was%20already%20home%20to%20an%20Arab%20population%20that%20had%20lived%20there%20for%20centuries.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20were%2C%20therefore%2C%20two%20peoples%20and%20one%20land%2C%20hence%20the%20conflict.%20Are%20you%20also%20suggesting%2C%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20that%20the%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20was%20not%20justified%20or%20was%20at%20least%20based%20on%20weak%20grounds%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20was%20based%20on%20exceptionally%20weak%20grounds%20and%20a%20misrepresentation%20of%20the%20reality%20in%20Palestine%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20There%20was%20a%20very%20clever%20Zionist%20slogan%3A%20a%20country%20without%20a%20people%20for%20a%20people%20without%20a%20country.%20The%20slogan%20implied%20that%20the%20Jews%20were%20people%20without%20a%20country%2C%20which%20they%20were%2C%20but%20it%20also%20implied%20that%20Palestine%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20people%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20inhabited%20but%20this%20was%20not%20true.%20There%20had%20been%20a%20well-constituted%20Arab%20society%20in%20Palestine%20for%20centuries.%20And%20the%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20was%20also%20not%20very%20convincing%20because%20Zionism%20was%20a%20secular%20movement%2C%20but%20it%20also%20invoked%20divine%20promise%20to%20the%20Jews%20of%20the%20promised%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20zionists%20were%20secular%2C%20they%20did%20not%20believe%20in%20God%20and%20yet%20they%20turned%20God%20into%20a%20land%20agent%20who%20promised%20them%20this%20particular%20plot%20of%20land.%20The%20weakness%20of%20the%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20is%20illustrated%20by%20the%20following%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20visionary%20of%20the%20Jewish%20state%20was%20Theodore%20Herzl%2C%20a%20Viennese%20Jew%2C%20who%20wrote%20a%20pamphlet%20outlining%20his%20idea%20for%20a%20Jewish%20state%20in%20Palestine%2C%20and%20the%20rabbis%20of%20Vienna%20got%20together%2C%20collected%20some%20money%2C%20and%20sent%20two%20of%20their%20members%20to%20Palestine%20to%20check%20out%20Herzl%E2%80%99s%20idea%20and%20the%20two%20rabbis%20sent%20a%20telegram%20which%20became%20famous.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20bride%20is%20beautiful%20but%20she%20is%20already%20married%20to%20another%20man.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Palestine%20is%20beautiful%20but%20there%20were%20already%20other%20people%20living%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20As%20a%20historian%2C%20how%20do%20you%20evaluate%20a%20more%20emotional%20claim%20that%20the%20Jews%20make%20to%20the%20land%20of%20Palestine%20that%20it%20is%20their%20biblical%20heritage%3F%20That%20it%20is%20the%20land%20of%20Canaan.%20This%20is%20where%20Judaism%20started.%20Therefore%2C%20this%20is%20our%20home.%20How%20do%20you%20evaluate%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20This%20claim%20is%20completely%20invalid%20in%20the%20modern%20era.%20In%20the%20modern%20era%2C%20there%20is%20international%20law%2C%20there%20are%20international%20organisations%2C%20there%20are%20international%20borders%2C%20and%20a%20claim%20that%20goes%20back%20to%20two%20millennia%20ago%20is%20completely%20untenable%20in%20the%20modern%20age.%20Because%20any%20other%20people%20could%20resurrect%20claims%20that%20go%20back%20millennia%20ago%2C%20and%20if%20every%20person%20was%20able%20to%20assert%20historic%20rights%20to%20a%20land%2C%20then%20that%20is%20a%20recipe%20for%20never-ending%20conflict%20all%20over%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHaving%20said%20that%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20deny%20the%20very%20strong%20emotional%20and%20historic%20association%20between%20the%20Jewish%20people%20and%20Zion.%20Zion%20is%20one%20of%20the%20many%20names%20for%20Jerusalem%2C%20so%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20deny%20the%20association%20and%20of%20course%2C%20Jerusalem%20is%20particularly%20of%20huge%20symbolic%20and%20religious%20importance%20to%20the%20Jewish%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJews%20for%20centuries%20have%20been%20praying%2C%20Jews%20everywhere%20have%20been%20praying%20in%20Jerusalem.%20That%20was%20the%20ultimate%20aspiration%20to%20return%20to%20Zion%2C%20but%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20a%20politically%20or%20legally%20valid%20claim%20to%20the%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20Israel%20came%20into%20being%2C%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20in%201948%20and%20that%20very%20quickly%20led%20to%20the%20expulsion%20of%20some%20750%2C000%20Palestinians%20from%20their%20lands%2C%20which%20they%20called%20the%20%3Cem%3Enakba%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20an%20article%20that%20you%20wrote%20for%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fi%3E%20in%202009%2C%20you%20said%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%20here%2C%20%E2%80%9CEstablishing%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20in%20May%201948%20involved%20a%20monumental%20injustice%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%E2%80%9D%20Was%20that%20the%20start%20of%20the%20modern-day%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%20as%20well%20as%20the%20deep-seated%20sense%20of%20hurt%20and%20grievance%20that%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20feel%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%5BIn%5D%201948%2C%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20and%20the%20first%20Arab-Israeli%20War%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20the%20modern%20history%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20choose%20that%20year%20to%20mark%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20to%20choose%20an%20arbitrary%20date%20for%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20I%20would%20opt%20for%201917.%20That%20is%20the%20year%20in%20which%20Britain%20issued%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FBalfour-Declaration%5C%22%3EBalfour%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20support%20of%20a%20national%20home%20for%20the%20Jewish%20people%20in%20Palestine.%20So%2C%20this%20is%20a%20really%20significant%20document%20in%20which%20Britain%20allocated%20to%20the%20Jews%20political%20right%2C%20the%20right%20to%20national%20self-determination%2C%20and%20denied%20it%20to%20the%20Arabs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201917%2C%20the%20Jews%20were%20only%2010%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20the%20Arabs%20were%2090%25.%20The%20Jews%20owned%20only%202%25%20of%20the%20land%2C%20and%20yet%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20enabled%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20to%20embark%20on%20the%20systematic%20takeover%20of%20Palestine%20which%20continues%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20would%20say%20that%20the%20British%20mandate%20in%20Palestine%20from%201922%20to%201948%20is%20what%20enabled%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20to%20establish%20itself%2C%20and%20%5Bit%20also%20enabled%20them%5D%20to%20eventually%2C%20in%201948%2C%20proclaim%20and%20achieve%20independence.%20Now%2C%20I%20have%20never%20questioned%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20within%20its%20original%20borders.%20These%20are%20the%20borders%20that%20were%20agreed%20upon%20between%20Israel%20and%20its%20neighbours%20in%201949%20after%20the%20guns%20fell%20silent.%20These%20are%20the%20only%20internationally%20recognised%20borders%20that%20Israel%20has%20ever%20had%20and%20the%20ones%20that%20I%20still%20regard%20as%20legitimate%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20denying%20that%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20involved%20a%20monumental%20injustice%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%20This%20is%20what%20the%20Palestinians%20call%20the%20%3Cem%3Enakba%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20catastrophe.%20Three-fourths%20of%20a%20million%20Palestinians%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20Arab%20population%20became%20refugees%2C%20and%20the%20name%20Palestine%20was%20wiped%20off%20the%20map.%20This%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3ENakba%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20this%20is%20the%20catastrophe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EI%E2%80%99ll%20just%20point%20out%20for%20the%20audience%2C%20professor%20Shlaim%2C%20that%20although%20you%20accept%20that%201948%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20history%2C%20the%20actual%20origin%20of%20the%20problem%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20Balfour%20Declaration%20of%201917%2C%20which%20is%20why%20many%20Palestinians%20believe%20that%20the%20original%20responsibility%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20Israel%2C%20and%20for%20the%20problems%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20British%20responsibility%20and%20you%20explained%20that%20very%20well.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20years%20that%20followed%201948%2C%20the%20Arab%20nations%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20rejected%20Israel.%20They%20fought%20wars%20with%20Israel%2C%20but%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FSix-Day-War%5C%22%3ESix-Day%20War%20of%201967%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Israel%20captured%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%2C%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20and%20the%20Golan%20Heights%2C%20it%20agreed%20to%20trade%20land%20for%20peace.%20That%20could%20have%20led%20to%20a%20solution%2C%20but%20Israel%20reneged%20on%20its%20commitments%20and%20instead%20started%20to%20build%20settlements%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories.%20Of%20this%2C%20you%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9Crefusal%20to%20relinquish%20the%20fruits%20of%20its%20military%20victory%20turned%20little%20Israel%20into%20a%20colonial%20power%20ruling%20over%20a%20recalcitrant%20Arab%20population.%E2%80%9D%20Why%20did%20Israel%20do%20this%3F%20Why%20did%20it%20deliberately%20throw%20away%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20solution%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20June%201967%20war%20was%20another%20historic%20turning%20point%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Israel%20had%20something%20concrete%20that%20it%20could%20offer%20to%20the%20Arabs%20in%20return%20for%20peace%2C%20because%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Israel%20travelled%20%5Bexpanded%5D%20its%20territory.%20It%20captured%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20from%20Syria%2C%20the%20West%20Bank%20from%20Jordan%2C%20and%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%20from%20Egypt.%20And%20the%20King%20Hussein%20of%20Jordan%2C%20immediately%20after%20the%20end%20of%20hostilities%2C%20offered%20Israel%20total%20peace%20for%20total%20withdrawal.%20But%20Israel%20did%20not%20accept%20this%20offer%2C%20and%20Israel%20started%20building%20settlements%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20and%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20in%20the%20Golan%20Heights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhy%20did%20Israel%20not%20agree%20to%20trade%20land%20for%20peace%2C%20now%20that%20it%20had%20the%20opportunity%3F%20The%20answer%20to%20that%20is%2C%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20victory%2C%20there%20was%20a%20convergence%20of%20secular%20nationalism%20with%20religious%20nationalism%2C%20and%20both%20secular%20Israelis%20and%20religious%20Israelis%20felt%20that%20this%20was%20an%20opportunity%20to%20realise%20the%20land%20of%20Israel.%20The%20land%20of%20Israel%20was%20a%20concept%2C%20and%20now%20they%20wanted%20to%20turn%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20into%20the%20land%20of%20Israel%2C%20by%20incorporating%20the%20West%20Bank%20into%20Greater%20Israel.%20The%20West%20Bank%2C%20or%20as%20right-wing%20Israelis%20prefer%20to%20call%20it%2C%20Judea%20and%20Samaria%2C%20prefer%20the%20biblical%20rights.%20So%2C%20it%20was%20the%20surge%20of%20powerful%20nationalism%20in%20Israel%20that%20militated%20against%20a%20compromise%2C%20and%20the%20settlements%20are%20one%20of%20the%20factors%20that%20have%20not%20only%20been%20illegal%2C%20but%20also%20remain%20the%20main%20obstacle%20to%20peace%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20this%20a%20missed%20opportunity%3F%20%5BWas%20it%5D%20A%20moment%20when%20Israel%20could%20actually%20have%20established%20a%20peaceful%20relationship%20with%20its%20Arab%20neighbours%3F%20Did%20it%20miss%20the%20opportunity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EMost%20definitely%2C%20it%20was%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Israel.%20The%20United%20Nations%20offered%20a%20formula%20for%20a%20settlement.%20UN%20Resolution%20242%20offered%20Israel%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20return%20for%20giving%20up%20the%20territories%20it%20had%20conquered%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20formula%20that%20%5Bhad%5D%20worked.%20When%20Israel%20%5Bhad%5D%20applied%20the%20formula%20242%2C%20in%201979%2C%20it%20got%20a%20peace%20agreement%20with%20Egypt.%20Israel%20had%20to%20give%20back%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%2C%20but%20in%20return%20it%20got%20peace.%20Israel%20could%20have%20had%20peace%20with%20Syria%20if%20it%20had%20agreed%20to%20return%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20to%20Syrian%20sovereignty.%20And%20as%20I%20just%20said%2C%20King%20Hussein%20of%20Jordan%20also%20offered%20Israel%20land%20for%20peace%2C%20but%20Israel%20missed%20the%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%201967%2C%20Israel%20had%20a%20basic%20choice%20to%20make%2C%20land%20or%20peace%20with%20its%20neighbours%2C%20and%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20Israel%20has%20opted%20for%20land%2C%20in%20preference%20to%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing-300x202.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing-1024x689.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681847%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22807%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPalestinians%20fleeing%20their%20homes%20after%20the%20establishment%20of%20Israel%20in%201948.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FDavid%20Eldan%2FCC%20BY-SA%203.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20next%20opportunity%20for%20a%20solution%2C%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20came%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1993-2000%2Foslo%5C%22%3E1993%20Oslo%20Accords%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9COslo%20achieved%20three%20things%2C%20the%20PLO%20recognised%20Israel%2C%20Israel%20recognised%20the%20PLO%20as%20the%20representative%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20and%20the%20two%20sides%20agreed%20to%20resolve%20their%20outstanding%20differences%20by%20peaceful%20means.%E2%80%9D%20This%20led%20the%20Palestinians%20to%20believe%20that%20they%20could%20gain%20an%20independent%20state%20with%20a%20capital%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20but%20this%20never%20happened.%20What%20went%20wrong%3F%20And%20who%2C%20in%20your%20opinion%2C%20is%20more%20to%20blame%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Oslo%20Accord%20which%20happened%2030%20years%20ago%20last%20month%20was%20a%20very%20modest%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%20and%20at%20the%20time%2C%20when%20the%20Oslo%20Accord%20was%20signed%2C%20I%20was%20euphoric.%20I%20thought%20that%20this%20is%20the%20real%20deal%2C%20%5Bthat%5D%20this%20is%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20solution%2C%20because%20I%20believed%20that%20it%20would%20start%20a%20process%20of%20gradual%20controlled%20Israeli%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20occupied%20territories%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20which%20there%20would%20be%20a%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20but%20I%20was%20wrong.%20Now%2C%20the%20Oslo%20Peace%20process%20broke%20down.%20Why%20did%20it%20break%20down%3F%20There%20are%20two%20different%20explanations%3A%20there%20is%20the%20official%20Israeli%20explanation%2C%20which%20says%20Oslo%20broke%20down%20because%20the%20Palestinians%20returned%20to%20violence%2C%20and%20it%20is%20terrorism%20that%20destroyed%20the%20Accord.%20And%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20never%20accepted%20the%20Oslo%20Accord%2C%20and%20so%20he%20rejected%20it%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20explanation%20is%20that%20it%20is%20Israel%20%E2%80%93%20which%20after%20the%20murder%20of%20Yitzhak%20Rabin%2C%20and%20the%20return%20to%20power%20of%20the%20Likud%20right-wing%20party%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20in%201996%20%E2%80%93%20that%20reneged%20on%20its%20side%20of%20the%20deal.%20And%20if%20you%20press%20me%20to%20say%20in%20one%20word%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Oslo%20Peace%20process%2C%20that%20word%20is%20%E2%80%98settlements%E2%80%99.%20Jewish%20settlements%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%20represent%20land%20grabbing%2C%20stealing%20land%20that%20belongs%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%20Land%20grabbing%20and%20peacemaking%20don%E2%80%99t%20go%20together%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20one%20or%20the%20other%2C%20and%20by%20constantly%20expanding%20settlements%2C%20Israel%20showed%20that%20it%20prefers%20land%20to%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-palestine-jewish-voice-for-peace-apartheid%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Not%20in%20Our%20Name%E2%80%99%3A%20The%20Jews%20Who%20Refuse%20to%20Be%20Bystanders%20to%20Historic%20Injustice%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20quote%20from%20your%20writings.%20You%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20change%20of%20government%20from%20Labor%20to%20Likud%20had%20profound%20implications%20for%20the%20peace%20process%20and%20the%20reason%20is%2C%20Likud%20explicitly%20rejected%20the%20idea%20of%20an%20independent%20Palestinian%20state%20alongside%20Israel.%E2%80%9D%20And%20the%20Likud%20leader%20was%20none%20other%20than%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu.%20So%2C%20does%20he%20bear%20a%20certain%20measure%20of%20personal%20responsibility%20because%20of%20the%20position%20he%20took%2C%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20collapsed%20and%20were%20not%20fulfilled%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3ENetanyahu%20bears%20a%20very%20very%20large%20share%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20because%20when%20he%20was%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%2C%20he%20led%20a%20campaign%20of%20incitement%20against%20the%20Rabin%20government%2C%20the%20democratically%20elected%20government%2C%20and%20this%20incitement%20ended%20with%20the%20assassination%20of%20Yitzhak%20Rabin.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20he%20was%20never%20committed%20to%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%2C%20and%20once%20he%20was%20elected%20in%201996%2C%20and%20he%20was%20elected%20by%20a%20margin%20of%20less%20than%201%25%2C%20and%20yet%20he%20immediately%20proceeded%20to%20undermine%20and%20subvert%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20and%20reestablish%20Israeli%20control%20over%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELabour%20built%20settlements%20only%20in%20areas%20that%20they%20thought%20were%20strategically%20important.%20The%20Likud%20under%20Netanyahu%20has%20built%20settlements%20across%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20the%20West%20Bank%20in%20order%20to%20make%20territorial%20compromise%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20fact%2C%20you%20make%20this%20point%20very%20strongly%20in%20your%20work.%20Since%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%2C%20Israeli%20settlements%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%20have%20proliferated%20to%20the%20point%20that%20there%20are%20now%20some%20750%2C000%20settlers%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%20In%20Gaza%2C%20Israel%20occupied%20the%20Strip%2C%20then%20after%20vacating%20it%2C%20blockaded%20it%20and%20surrounded%20it%20virtually%20from%20all%20sides%2C%20restricting%20imports%20and%20exports.%20And%20even%20when%20it%20took%20over%20the%20whole%20of%20Jerusalem%20as%20its%20capital%2C%20it%20once%20again%20gave%20a%20signal%20that%20there%20was%20no%20question%20of%20Jerusalem%20being%20shared.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoes%20this%20mean%20that%20in%20the%20last%2010-15%20years%2C%20maybe%20a%20bit%20longer%2C%20Israel%20has%20effectively%20buried%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20deep%20underground%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIt%20does%20mean%20that%20Israel%20has%20completely%20turned%20its%20back%20on%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%2C%20and%20if%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20intention%2C%20if%20its%20purpose%20was%20to%20proceed%20to%20peace%20with%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20then%20it%20would%20support%20a%20strong%20and%20united%20Palestinian%20leadership%2C%20but%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20policy%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20five%20terms%20of%20Netanyahu%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20has%20always%20been%20divide%20and%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhenever%20the%20Palestinians%20managed%20to%20reconcile%20their%20differences%2C%20to%20form%20a%20national%20unity%20government%2C%20which%20included%20Hamas%20and%20Fatah%2C%20Israel%20launched%20an%20operation%20which%20disrupted%20the%20national%20unity%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20by%20its%20actions%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20is%20not%20interested%20in%20having%20a%20Palestinian%20partner%20for%20peace%20because%20it%20wants%20to%20maintain%20its%20control%20over%20the%20territory.%20In%202005%2C%20Israel%20withdrew%20unilaterally%20from%20Gaza%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20for%20its%20own%20reasons%2C%20not%20part%20of%20an%20overall%20settlement%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-asks-india-to-declare-hamas-as-a-terrorist-organisation%5C%22%3EIsrael%20Asks%20India%20to%20Declare%20Hamas%20as%20a%20Terrorist%20Organisation%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20I%20pause%20you%20there%20Professor%20Shlaim%3F%20We%E2%80%99re%20going%20into%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20story%2C%20which%20is%20another%20very%20important%20chapter%2C%20but%20there%20are%20some%20details%20which%20my%20audience%20may%20not%20be%20aware%20of.%20So%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20go%20to%20the%20beginning%20of%20that%2C%20so%20it%20helps%20an%20Indian%20audience%2C%20who%E2%80%99s%20unfamiliar%20with%20it%2C%20understand.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHamas%20was%20founded%20in%201987%20as%20an%20organisation%20committed%20to%20the%20physical%20elimination%20of%20Israel.%20Before%20we%20go%20further%2C%20how%20would%20you%20characterise%20or%20describe%20Hamas%3F%20And%20how%20would%20you%20explain%20its%20ideology%2C%20in%20particular%20the%20goals%20and%20principles%20it%20stands%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EHamas%20is%20an%20Islamic%20resistance%20movement%2C%20and%20Hamas%20emerged%20in%201987%20during%20the%20First%20Palestinian%20Intifada%20or%20uprising%2C%20and%20curiously%2C%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20Israel%20supported%20Hamas%20as%20a%20counterweight%20to%20the%20secular%20nationalism%20of%20the%20PLO%2C%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20national%20movement.%20So%2C%20Israel%20had%20already%20begun%20to%20play%20the%20game%20of%20divide%20and%20rule%2C%20but%20Hamas%20is%20an%20Islamic%20resistance%20movement%20to%20the%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20and%20in%202006%2C%20it%20won%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election.%20It%20won%20an%20absolute%20majority%20in%20an%20all-Palestine%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20we%20go%20into%20that%20detail%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20you%20described%20Hamas%20very%20carefully%20as%20an%20Islamic%20resistance%20movement%20to%20the%20Israeli%20occupation.%20Many%20people%20today%20insist%20upon%20calling%20Hamas%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20but%20you%20did%20not.%20Is%20it%20%5Ba%20terrorist%20organisation%3F%5D%20Or%20has%20it%20become%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20since%20its%20foundation%3F%20Or%20is%20that%20only%20partly%20correct%20or%20is%20it%20incorrect%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20political%20leadership%20of%20Hamas%20which%20most%20certainly%20is%20not%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20political%20leadership%20that%20adopted%20the%20parliamentary%20road%20to%20power%20and%20won%20the%20election%20in%20January%202006.%20But%20Hamas%20also%20has%20a%20military%20wing%2C%20and%20the%20military%20wing%20has%20committed%20terrorist%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%20on%20October%207%2C%20it%20launched%20an%20attack%20inside%20Israel%2C%20which%20involved%20a%20massacre%20of%20Israeli%20civilians.%20Attacking%20civilians%20is%20wrong%2C%20killing%20civilians%20is%20wrong%2C%20period.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20debate%20about%20it.%20Whether%20Hamas%20kills%20Israeli%20civilians%2C%20that%20is%20wrong%2C%20and%20if%20Israel%20kills%20Palestinian%20civilians%2C%20as%20it%20is%20doing%20today%20in%20Gaza%2C%20that%20is%20equally%20wrong%2C%20and%20I%20would%20denounce%20it%20as%20state%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20a%20distinction%20between%20the%20political%20wing%20of%20Hamas%20and%20the%20military%20wing.%20The%20political%20wing%20%E2%80%93%20as%20you%20were%20saying%20and%20we%E2%80%99ll%20talk%20about%20it%20further%20in%20detail%20%E2%80%93%20won%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20in%202006%20and%20came%20to%20power.%20But%20the%20military%20wing%20has%20been%20indulging%20from%20time%20to%20time%20in%20terrorist%20acts.%20So%20is%20the%20military%20wing%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20military%20wing%20is%20the%20element%20of%20a%20political%20movement%20of%20a%20political%20party%20and%20that%20military%20wing%20has%20committed%20terrorist%20acts%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20I%20am%20reluctant%20to%20describe%20it%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation.%20I%20would%20like%20to%20examine%20its%20actions%20case%20by%20case%2C%20and%20conclude%20that%20if%20it%20attacks%20civilians%2C%20then%20that%20is%20a%20terrorist%20act%2C%20but%20if%20it%20attacks%20Israeli%20military%20targets%20or%20Israeli%20soldiers%2C%20then%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20call%20it%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20I%20would%20say%20that%20people%20under%20occupation%20have%20the%20right%20to%20resist%20under%20international%20law%2C%20and%20Hamas%20is%20exercising%20the%20right%20to%20resist%20the%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20element%20within%20the%20Palestinian%20community%20that%20is%20resisting%20the%20occupation%20because%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20in%20Ramallah%20is%20a%20collaborationist%20body.%20It%20collaborates%20with%20Israel%20in%20perpetuating%20the%20occupation.%20So%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20a%20subcontractor%20for%20Israeli%20security%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it%20has%20lost%20legitimacy%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20In%202006%20January%2C%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20were%20held%20both%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%2C%20and%20Hamas%20unexpectedly%20won%20a%20decisive%20victory%20over%20Fatah%2C%20but%20when%20Hamas%20formed%20the%20government%2C%20Israel%20refused%20to%20recognise%20it%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20did%20the%20same.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20in%20November%202007%2C%20when%20Fatah%20and%20Hamas%20formed%20a%20government%20of%20national%20unity%20overcoming%20their%20differences%20and%20getting%20together%2C%20you%20are%20saying%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%20plotted%20to%20undermine%20it.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20this%20Israeli%20attitude%20to%20Hamas%20justified%20by%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%201987%20position%20of%20wanting%20to%20eliminate%20Israel%3F%20Or%20was%20Hamas%20changing%20its%20attitude%3F%20And%20did%20Israel%20fail%20to%20realise%20the%20change%2C%20and%20thus%20miss%20another%20opportunity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EPolitical%20movements%20and%20movements%20on%20national%20liberation%20evolve%20just%20as%20the%20PLO%20evolved%20from%20an%20absolute%20rejection%20of%20Israel%20to%20a%20much%20more%20moderate%20position%20that%20culminated%20in%20signing%20the%20Oslo%20Accord%20with%20Israel.%20Hamas%20is%20a%20political%20movement%20which%20has%20moderated%20its%20position%20since%20the%20Charter%20of%201988%2C%20which%20is%20a%20very%20dogmatic%20and%20even%20anti-semitic%20document%2C%20but%20once%20it%20was%20elected%2C%20Hamas%20seriously%20moderated%20its%20position.%20It%20formed%20a%20coalition%20government%20with%20Fatah%2C%20the%20government%20called%20for%20negotiations%20with%20Israel%20for%20a%20long-term%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20refused%20to%20recognise%20the%20Hamas-made%20government%20and%20it%20engaged%20in%20economic%20warfare%20to%20break%20it%20down.%20The%20United%20States%20and%20European%20Union%2C%20to%20their%20shame%2C%20supported%20Israel%20in%20this%20effort%20to%20work%20with%20the%20Hamas-led%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20Western%20powers%20claim%20that%20they%E2%80%99re%20there%20to%20promote%20democracy%2C%20and%20what%20happened%20there%20shows%20how%20hypocritical%20they%20were%2C%20because%20they%20say%20they%20want%20to%20promote%20democracy%20but%20when%20the%20Palestinians%20chose%20the%20wrong%20bunch%20of%20people%20they%20turned%20against%20Hamas%2C%20and%20there%20was%20indeed%20a%20plot%20which%20involved%20Israel%2C%20America%2C%20Fatah%20and%20Egyptian%20intelligence%2C%20to%20isolate%20Hamas%2C%20to%20weaken%20it%2C%20and%20eventually%20to%20overthrow%20it.%20There%20was%20a%20plan%20to%20carry%20out%20a%20coup%20to%20drive%20Hamas%20out%20of%20power%2C%20and%20this%20led%20Hamas%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20violent%20seizure%20of%20power%20in%20Gaza%20in%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20I%20pause%20you%20there%20for%20a%20moment%20Professor%20Shlaim%3F%20Why%20did%20Israel%20take%20this%20attitude%20to%20Hamas%3F%20Was%20it%20because%20Israel%20failed%20to%20realise%20that%20Hamas%20had%20evolved%3F%20That%20is%2C%20Israel%20was%20ignorant%20of%20the%20change%20and%20evolution%20taking%20place%2C%20or%20did%20it%20simply%20turn%20a%20blind%20eye%20and%20refuse%20to%20accept%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIsrael%20refuses%20to%20accept%20Hamas%20as%20a%20negotiating%20partner.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20position%20is%20that%20Hamas%20is%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20%E2%80%93%20pure%20and%20simple.%20It%20will%20never%20negotiate%20with%20it.%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20policy%20has%20been%20to%20let%20Hamas%20rule%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20but%20to%20contain%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20and%20this%20policy%20collapsed%2C%20because%20Gaza%20could%20not%20be%20contained.%20What%20Israel%20refuses%20to%20do%20is%20to%20accept%20that%20Hamas%20represents%20a%20serious%20body%20of%20Palestinians%20and%20that%20you%20cannot%20reach%20any%20peace%20agreement%20with%20the%20Palestinians%20that%20excludes%20Hamas.%20So%2C%20the%20sensible%20thing%20for%20Israel%20to%20do%20and%20the%20other%20European%20powers%20to%20do%20is%20to%20recognise%20Hamas%20and%20negotiate%20with%20Hamas%20for%20a%20political%20settlement%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-in-a-gaza-hospital-no-power-lack-of-medicines-many-operations-happening-without-anesthesia%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20In%20a%20Gaza%20Hospital%2C%20No%20Power%2C%20Lack%20of%20Medicines%2C%20Many%20Operations%20Happening%20Without%20Anesthesia%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20you%20write%20that%20to%20preempt%20the%20coup%20of%20the%20plot%20which%20you%20were%20talking%20about%20a%20moment%20ago%2C%20one%20in%20which%20Egyptian%20intelligence%2C%20Israel%2C%20the%20United%20States%20were%20all%20involved%2C%20Hamas%20violently%20seized%20power%20in%20Gaza%20in%202007.%20That%20not%20only%20divided%20the%20Palestinian%20movement%20between%20Fatah%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20but%20it%20also%20set%20up%20the%20Hamas-Israel%20conflict%20that%E2%80%99s%20virtually%20lasted%20since%20then.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20talk%20about%20that%20conflict.%20Israel%20accuses%20Hamas%20of%20repeated%20terrorist%20attacks%20causing%20Israeli%20deaths.%20Hamas%20accuses%20Israel%20of%20blockading%20the%20Strip%2C%20depriving%20its%20people%20of%20development%2C%20and%20periodic%20air%20strikes%20and%20even%20frequent%20or%20at%20least%20occasional%20ground%20invasions.%20How%20do%20you%2C%20as%20a%20historian%2C%20view%20the%20decade%20and%20a%20half%20since%202007%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EA%20decade%20and%20a%20half%20since%202007%20has%20not%20involved%20any%20movement%2C%20any%20step%20towards%20a%20peaceful%20settlement%20of%20the%20conflict.%20This%20is%20a%20political%20conflict%20between%20the%20two%20sides%2C%20but%20Israel%20only%20uses%20brute%20military%20force%20to%20suppress%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20nothing%20but%20brute%20military%20force.%20There%20is%20an%20Israeli%20saying%20that%2C%20if%20force%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20use%20more%20force%2C%20but%20this%20is%20completely%20ludicrous.%20Military%20force%20cannot%20solve%20the%20political%20dispute%20between%20the%20two%20sides%2C%20and%20Israeli%20generals%20have%20a%20phrase%2C%20%E2%80%98to%20mow%20the%20lawn%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98to%20cut%20the%20grass%2C%E2%80%99%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20horrific%20metaphor%20because%20what%20it%20means%20is%2C%20that%20every%20few%20years%20Israel%20goes%20into%20Gaza%20with%20very%20advanced%20weaponry%2C%20great%20technology%2C%20and%20really%20inflicts%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20damage%2C%20not%20just%20on%20Hamas%20and%20its%20military%20capabilities%2C%20but%20also%20on%20civilians%20and%20the%20civilian%20infrastructure.%20%E2%80%98Mowing%20the%20lawn%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20mechanical%20thing%20that%20you%20do%20every%20now%20and%20again%20to%20set%20back%20Gaza%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tunnel.%20So%2C%20what%20Israel%20needs%20to%20do%20is%20to%20offer%20a%20political%20horizon%20and%20hope%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%2C%20you%20write%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%E2%80%99s%20propaganda%20machine%20persistently%20pervades%20the%20notion%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20are%20terrorists%2C%20that%20they%20reject%20coexistence%20with%20the%20Jewish%20state%2C%20that%20their%20nationalism%20is%20little%20more%20than%20anti-Semitism%2C%20that%20Hamas%20is%20just%20a%20bunch%20of%20religious%20fanatics%2C%20and%20that%20Islam%20is%20incompatible%20with%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20you%20suggesting%20that%20this%20is%20not%20just%20deliberate%20misrepresentation%20but%20pretty%20close%20to%20an%20outright%20lie%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EOf%20course%2C%20because%20this%20is%20Israeli%20propaganda.%20It%E2%80%99s%20completely%20one-sided%2C%20and%20it%20completely%20ignores%20what%20we%20have%20talked%20about%20before%2C%20that%20Hamas%20chose%20the%20parliamentary%20road%20to%20power.%20Hamas%20tried%20a%20political%20avenue%20and%20every%20avenue%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20explore%20is%20blocked%20by%20Israel%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20easy%20for%20Israel%20to%20dismiss%20any%20action%20by%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20terrorist%20action%2C%20anything%20by%20Palestinians%2C%20but%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20are%20a%20normal%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20want%20what%20every%20normal%20person%20wants%2C%20which%20is%20to%20live%20in%20freedom%20and%20dignity%20on%20their%20own%20land%2C%20and%20it%20is%20Israel%20which%20is%20preventing%20them%20from%20doing%20that.%20Moreover%2C%20Israel%20has%20launched%20successive%20attacks%20on%20Gaza%2C%20the%20first%20one%20was%20Operation%20Cast%20Lead%20in%202008.%20By%20my%20count%2C%20the%20current%20round%20of%20violence%20is%20the%20sixth%20Israeli%20assault%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%2C%20and%20all%20Israel%20has%20to%20offer%20is%20more%20force%20and%20demonisation%20of%20the%20Palestinians.%20Israel%20systematically%20demonises%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20all%20Palestinians%20as%20terrorists%2C%20and%20the%20danger%20of%20dehumanising%20a%20whole%20people%20is%20that%20it%20paves%20the%20way%20to%20ethnic%20cleansing%20and%20genocide.%20What%20we%20are%20witnessing%20today%2C%20day%20after%20day%2C%20in%20Gaza%20is%20Israel%20moving%20towards%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20the%20population%20and%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3ENow%20you%20have%20made%20another%20very%20important%20point%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%20here%3A%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%20claimed%20to%20be%20the%20victim%20of%20Palestinian%20violence.%E2%80%9D%20The%20truth%20you%20pointed%20out%20is%20very%20different.%20You%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20conflict%20between%20David%20and%20Goliath%2C%20but%20the%20biblical%20image%20was%20inverted.%20A%20small%20and%20defenceless%20Palestinian%20David%20faced%20a%20heavily%20armed%2C%20merciless%2C%20and%20overpowering%20Israeli%20Goliath.%E2%80%9D%20I%20have%20to%20tell%20you%2C%20when%20I%20read%20that%20sentence%2C%20I%20said%20to%20myself%2C%20this%20is%20definitely%20not%20how%20the%20West%20views%20the%20problem.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20Western%20perception.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Western%20perception%20of%20the%20conflict%20is%20completely%20out%20of%20touch%20with%20reality%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20obvious%20to%20anyone%20who%20has%20eyes%2C%20to%20see%20that%20the%20victims%20in%20this%20conflict%20are%20not%20the%20Israelis%2C%20but%20they%20are%20the%20Palestinians.%20This%20is%20indeed%20a%20conflict%20between%20a%20Palestinian%20David%20and%20a%20heavily%20armed%20and%20overbearing%20Israeli%20Goliath%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20asymmetry%20of%20power%20between%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20the%20Israelis%20that%20militates%20against%20a%20peaceful%20solution%20to%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20bears%20a%20large%20share%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20impasse%20between%20Israelis%20and%20the%20Palestinians%20because%20the%20West%20is%20completely%20one-sided%20in%20its%20support%20for%20Israel.%20America%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20gives%20Israel%20money%20and%20arms%2C%20and%20diplomatic%20protection.%20The%20trouble%20with%20American%20support%20for%20Israel%20is%20that%20it%20is%20unconditional%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20conditional%20on%20Israel%20obeying%20international%20law%2C%20or%20respecting%20Palestinian%20human%20rights.%20It%E2%80%99s%20this%20unconditional%20American%2C%20and%20British%2C%20and%20largely%20European%20Union%20support%20for%20Israel%20which%20enables%20Israel%20to%20get%20away%2C%20literally%20with%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20saw%20during%20this%20crisis%20that%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%20and%20other%20European%20leaders%20rushed%20to%20Israel%20to%20visit%2C%20to%20show%20their%20support%20for%20Israel%2C%20but%20they%20haven%E2%80%99t%20called%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%20Surely%2C%20the%20decent%20thing%20to%20do%20in%20the%20present%20situation%20is%20to%20call%20for%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20and%20Hamas%20has%20offered%20to%20release%20the%20civilian%20hostages%20in%20return%20for%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20but%20it%20is%20Israel%20that%20is%20refusing%20to%20stop%20its%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fde-escalation-ceasefire-among-phrases-to-avoid-in-press-materials-show-us-state-dept-emails%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98De-escalation%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Ceasefire%E2%80%99%20Among%20Phrases%20to%20Avoid%20in%20Press%20Materials%2C%20Show%20Us%20State%20Dept%20Emails%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%2C%20it%20was%20against%20this%20background%20which%20we%E2%80%99ve%20discussed%20in%20some%20detail%2C%20that%20Hamas%20launched%20its%20October%207%20attack.%20Does%20the%20history%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20discussed%20explain%20why%20that%20attack%20happened%3F%20Even%20if%20it%20certainly%20cannot%20justify%20it%20or%20even%20excuse%20it.%20And%20I%E2%80%99m%20making%20that%20clear%20to%20the%20audience%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20the%20history%20justifies%20or%20excuses%20the%20attack%2C%20but%20does%20it%20explain%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20in%20Israel%20has%20attracted%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20denunciation%20for%20a%20very%20good%20reason%2C%20because%20it%20was%20an%20attack%20on%20civilians.%20So%2C%20I%20denounce%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20Israeli%20civilians%20inside%20Israel%2C%20and%20much%20of%20the%20commentary%20speaks%20about%20October%207%20as%20a%20barbaric%20attack.%20What%20many%20commentators%20forget%20is%20that%20the%20conflict%20did%20not%20start%20on%20October%207.%20The%20conflict%20has%20to%20be%20seen%20against%2056%20years%20of%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20since%201967.%20The%20Israeli%20occupation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20lands%20is%20a%20daily%20violence%20against%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20and%20when%20Israel%20withdrew%20from%20Gaza%20unilaterally%20in%202005%2C%20it%20effectively%20turned%20Gaza%20into%20a%20prison%2C%20into%20the%20biggest%20open-air%20prison%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20imposed%20a%20blockade%2C%20already%20in%202007%2C%20a%20blockade%20of%20Gaza%20which%20is%20illegal%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20form%20of%20collective%20punishment.%20Now%20since%20October%207%2C%20Israel%20has%20intensified%20the%20blockade%20and%20committed%20war%20crimes%20by%20cutting%20off%20water%2C%20food%2C%20electricity%2C%20fuel%2C%20and%20medical%20supplies%20to%20the%20population%20of%20Gaza.%20So%2C%20the%20conflict%20didn%E2%80%99t%20start%20on%20October%207%20and%20the%20action%20by%20Hamas%20has%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20an%20act%20of%20resistance%20to%20the%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20and%20the%20history%20that%20we%20have%20reviewed%20briefly%20in%20our%20conversation.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20justify%20the%20attack%20of%20Hamas%20on%20October%207%2C%20but%20it%20surely%20gives%20the%20backdrop%20to%20what%20has%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20tries%20to%20contain%20the%20prison%20and%20now%20the%20prisoners%20have%20broken%20out%20of%20the%20prison.%20There%20is%20a%20Jewish-American%20writer%2C%20named%20Norman%20Finkelstein%2C%20who%20has%20described%20this%20as%20the%20revolt%20of%20the%20slaves.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20underdogs%20who%20have%20taken%20the%20initiative%20in%20breaking%20the%20siege.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20A%20sort%20of%20modern-day%20Spartacus.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIndeed%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20quite%20an%20interesting%20historical%20comparison%2C%20absolutely.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwearing-bracelets-to-avoid-a-mass-grave-a-palestinian-icon-bears-witness%5C%22%3EWearing%20Bracelets%20to%20Avoid%20a%20Mass%20Grave%3A%20A%20Palestinian%20Icon%20Bears%20Witness%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EIn%20your%20writing%2C%20you%20make%20three%20broad%20thematic%20points%20about%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict.%20First%2C%20you%20say%2C%20Israelis%20regard%20themselves%20as%20victims%2C%20but%20then%20you%20tellingly%20add%2C%20%5Bthat%20they%5D%20feeling%20themselves%20to%20be%20the%20victims%20tends%20to%20blind%20the%20Israeli%20majority%20to%20the%20suffering%20they%20inflict%20on%20the%20real%20victims%20in%20this%20conflict%2C%20the%20Palestinians.%20Are%20you%20saying%20that%20Israelis%20are%20oblivious%20to%2C%20or%20at%20least%2C%20blind%20to%20the%20sufferings%20they%20have%20inflicted%20on%20the%20Palestinians%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYes%2C%20and%20the%20Israeli%20media%20is%20a%20loyalist%20media%20that%20follows%20the%20party%20line%2C%20the%20government%20line%2C%20and%20there%20is%20very%20little%20reporting%20of%20what%20happens%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20hill%2C%20what%20happens%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories.%20So%2C%20Israelis%20are%20largely%20ignorant%20of%20what%20happens%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%20and%20they%20also%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20see%20themselves%20as%20victims.%20History%20explains%20why%20this%20should%20be%20so%2C%20the%20Jews%20have%20suffered%20a%20great%20deal%2C%20and%20the%20Jews%20endured%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20the%20Holocaust%20explains%20why%20Israelis%20are%20so%20obsessed%2C%20so%20concerned%2C%20almost%20obsessed%20with%20security%2C%20but%20this%20acute%20preoccupation%20with%20Israeli%20security%20does%20blind%20Israelis%20to%20the%20insecurity%20of%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20demands%20100%25%20security%20for%20itself.%20This%20translates%20into%20100%25%20insecurity%20for%20the%20Palestinians%20as%20we%E2%80%99re%20witnessing%20today%20in%20Gaza%2C%20so%20yes%2C%20the%20Israeli%20public%20is%20not%20well-informed%20about%20the%20rights%20and%20wrongs%2C%20or%20about%20the%20history%20of%20this%20conflict%2C%20and%20its%20leadership%2C%20especially%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%5Bwho%5D%20plays%20a%20major%20role%20in%20misinforming%20the%20public%20about%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20situation%20and%20about%20the%20legitimate%20rights%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25104243%2FPrime_Minister_of_Israel_Benjamin_Netanyahu.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221074%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25104243%2FPrime_Minister_of_Israel_Benjamin_Netanyahu.jpeg%20650w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25104243%2FPrime_Minister_of_Israel_Benjamin_Netanyahu-300x200.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664867%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22717%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2F%20Kremlin.ru%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20make%20another%20very%20important%20point%20about%20what%20you%20call%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20preoccupation%20with%20security%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%3A%20%E2%80%9CPreoccupation%20with%20security%20makes%20Israel%20susceptible%20to%20politicians%20who%20are%20unscrupulous%20enough%20to%20manipulate%20the%20sense%20of%20threat%20and%20inflate%20it%20for%20political%20advantage.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CThe%20arch%20manipulator%2C%E2%80%9D%20you%20say%2C%20is%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20is%20the%20high%20priest%20of%20fear%20who%20never%20stops%20harping%20on%20the%20existential%20threats%20facing%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoes%20this%20explain%20why%20he%20served%20for%2015%20or%2016%20years%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20longest%20ever%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20history%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThere%20are%20many%20reasons%20for%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20political%20success%20in%20being%20the%20longest-serving%20prime%20minister%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20history.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20them%2C%20but%20there%20are%20other%20factors%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20to%20focus%20for%20a%20moment%20on%20his%20manipulation%20of%20the%20sense%20of%20threat%20this%20is%20his%20hallmark.%20This%20is%20his%20most%20distinctive%20position%20to%20always%20exaggerate%20the%20existential%20threat%20to%20Israel%2C%20and%20for%20decades%20he%20has%20been%20saying%20that%20Iran%20poses%20an%20existential%20threat%20to%20Israel.%20Well%2C%20Iran%20doesn%E2%80%99t%2C%20Israel%20has%20a%20monopoly%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20and%20Israel%20threatens%20Iran.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20for%20this%20reason%20that%20the%20Iranians%20feel%20so%20strongly%20that%20they%20need%20to%20acquire%20nuclear%20weapons%20to%20counter%20the%20Israeli%20threat.%20So%2C%20Iran%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20existential%20threat%20to%20Israel%2C%20and%20Netanyahu%20has%20been%20saying%20repeatedly%20that%20Hamas%20poses%20an%20existential%20threat%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20Hamas%20doesn%E2%80%99t%2C%20Hamas%20is%20a%20very%20small%20poorly%20equipped%20organisation%2C%20which%20poses%20no%20threat%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20basic%20security%2C%20which%20engages%20in%20terrorism%20in%20pinpricks.%20And%20terrorism%20is%20the%20weapon%20of%20the%20weak.%20Netanyahu%20is%20a%20great%20manipulator%2C%20and%20also%20Netanyahu%20has%20misled%20the%20Israeli%20public%20into%20thinking%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20are%20finished%2C%20that%20Israel%20has%20defeated%20them%2C%20they%20are%20defeated%20people.%20Israel%20has%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20do%20whatever%20it%20likes%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20and%20Israel%20has%20effectively%20sealed%20Gaza%20off%20and%20it%20ceased%20to%20be%20a%20problem.%20The%20attack%20on%20October%207%20meant%20the%20collapse%20of%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20policy%20of%20dealing%20with%20the%20Palestinian%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20third%20broad%20thematic%20point%20I%20want%20to%20take%20up%20is%20the%20one%20you%20mentioned%20earlier%20in%20an%20answer.%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20the%20West.%20But%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20for%20me%20to%20repeat%20it%20for%20the%20audience.%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20what%20you%E2%80%99ve%20written%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Western%20policy%20of%20refusing%20to%20engage%20with%20Hamas%2C%20of%20supporting%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20abuse%20of%20the%20right%20to%20self-defence%2C%20and%20of%20supplying%20it%20with%20weapons%20that%20are%20repeatedly%20used%20to%20bomb%20a%20defenceless%20people%2C%20is%20morally%20indefensible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20are%20you%20saying%20that%20the%20West%20bears%20much%20of%20the%20blame%20for%20the%20repeated%20failure%20to%20resolve%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20problem%3F%20And%20perhaps%20also%20for%20the%20trauma%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20have%20had%20to%20live%20through%20for%20at%20least%2056%20years%2C%20if%20not%20a%20lot%20longer%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIsrael%20bears%20the%20largest%20part%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20dispossessing%20and%20oppressing%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%20The%20Israeli%20occupation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20territories%20is%20the%20most%20prolonged%20and%20brutal%20military%20occupation%20of%20modern%20times.%20But%20the%20West%20also%20bears%20a%20part%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20present%20and%20past%2C%20because%20of%20its%20massive%20support%20for%20Israel%2C%20its%20supply%20of%20arms%20to%20Israel%2C%20and%20its%20diplomatic%20protection%20of%20Israel.%20Britain%20and%20America%20use%20the%20veto%20at%20the%20Security%20Council%20to%20defeat%20every%20resolution%20that%20is%20critical%20of%20Israel%2C%20and%20Britain%20and%20America%20are%20opposed%20to%20the%20investigation%20by%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20of%20war%20crimes%20in%20the%20occupied%20Palestinian%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20very%20revealing.%20There%20is%20an%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20case%20for%20investigating%20war%20crimes%20both%20by%20Hamas%20and%20by%20Israel%2C%20and%20yet%20both%20Britain%20and%20America%20are%20opposed%20to%20the%20investigation%20of%20Israel%20in%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court.%20That%20means%20that%20they%20consider%20Israel%20to%20be%20above%20international%20law%20and%20above%20international%20scrutiny.%20This%20is%20why%20this%20unconditional%20character%2C%20this%20unconditional%20nature%20%5Bof%5D%20Western%20support%20for%20Israel%20is%20what%20accounts%20for%2C%20as%20I%20said%20earlier%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20Israel%20can%20act%20with%20impunity%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20Israel%20until%20now%20has%20been%20able%20to%20get%20away%2C%20literally%2C%20with%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20is%20committing%20murder%20on%20a%20massive%20scale%20every%20day%20in%20Gaza%2C%20but%20I%20have%20one%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20about%20the%20future%2C%20and%20that%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20complete%20disconnect%20between%20the%20Western%20government%20and%20the%20people%20of%20these%20Western%20countries.%20The%20governments%20are%20blindly%2C%20uncritically%20supportive%20of%20Israel%20whatever%20it%20does%2C%20but%20the%20people%20in%20America%2C%20and%20in%20Europe%2C%20and%20Britain%2C%20are%20increasingly%20and%20overwhelmingly%20pro-Palestinian.%20I%20hope%20that%20eventually%2C%20Western%20foreign%20policy%20will%20catch%20up%20with%20the%20sentiments%20of%20the%20people%20in%20the%20street.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20pick%20up%20briefly%2C%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20on%20something%20you%20said%20in%20that%20answer%2C%20and%20you%E2%80%99ve%20also%20written%20about%20it%20in%20a%20piece%20as%20recently%20as%20May%202019.%20That%20piece%20ends%20with%20the%20following%20sentence%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20the%20specific%20duty%20of%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20to%20hold%20Israel%20to%20account%20for%20the%20war%20crimes%20it%20committed%20in%20the%20past%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20ongoing%20assault%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20someone%20who%20served%20proudly%20and%20loyally%20in%20the%20Israeli%20Army%20in%20the%20mid-1960s%2C%20do%20you%20really%20mean%20that%20about%20your%20own%20country%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20served%20proudly%20and%20loyally%20in%20the%20IDF%20(Israeli%20Defence%20Forces)%20in%20the%20mid-1960s%20because%20at%20that%20time%20the%20IDF%20was%20true%20to%20its%20name.%20It%20was%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%2C%20it%20was%20a%20regular%20army%20that%20was%20there%20to%20defend%20the%20country%20against%20attack%20from%20the%20regular%20armies%20of%20the%20surrounding%20Arab%20states.%20Everything%20changed%20in%20June%201967.%20Israel%20travelled%20its%20territory%2C%20it%20occupied%20territory%20from%20all%20its%20neighbours%2C%20and%20my%20little%20army%20was%20changed%20and%20Israel%20became%20a%20brutal%20colonial%20power%20oppressing%20millions%20of%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20IDF%20was%20transformed%20into%20a%20brutal%20police%20force%20of%20a%20brutal%20colonial%20power.%20That%20is%20where%20I%20part%20away%20with%20Israel%2C%20but%20I%20emphasise%20again%2C%20that%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20question%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20legitimacy%20within%20its%201949%20armistice%20borders.%20What%20I%20reject%20totally%2C%20and%20reject%20completely%2C%20is%20the%20Zionist%20colonial%20project%20beyond%20the%20green%20line.%20And%20one%20last%20sentence%20about%20the%20ICC%2C%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20another%20illustration%20of%20Western%20double%20standards.%20The%20chief%20prosecutor%20instituted%20a%20full%20investigation%20of%20war%20crimes%20but%20the%20present%20chief%20prosecutor%20Karim%20Khan%2C%20a%20British%20barrister%2C%20has%20completely%20failed%20to%20make%20progress%20in%20that%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%2C%20within%20two%20days%2C%20he%20announced%20that%20he%20was%20going%20to%20institute%20a%20war%20crimes%20investigation%2C%20and%20within%20a%20week%2C%20he%20sent%20an%20advance%20team%20to%20Kyiv%20to%20start%20gathering%20the%20evidence%20for%20a%20war%20crimes%20investigation%20and%20trial.%20So%2C%20you%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20starker%20example%20of%20Western%20hypocrisy%20than%20condoning%20everything%2C%20all%20the%20war%20crimes%20that%20Israel%20commits%2C%20but%20supporting%20the%20ICC%20in%20its%20pursuit%20of%20Russian%20war%20crimes%20in%20the%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23162231%2FGaza-building.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23162231%2FGaza-building.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23162231%2FGaza-building-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23162231%2FGaza-building-1024x512.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23162231%2FGaza-building-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681396%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDamage%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20during%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war.%20Photo%3A%20Palestinian%20News%20%26amp%3B%20Information%20Agency%20(Wafa)%20in%20contract%20with%20APAimages%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20quick%20confirmation%20and%20one%20last%20question%20before%20I%20end.%20Do%20you%20believe%20%E2%80%93%20horrific%20and%20horrible%2C%20and%20indefensible%20as%20what%20Hamas%20did%20may%20have%20been%2C%20do%20you%20believe%20that%20the%20Israeli%20response%20on%20Gaza%20since%20October%207%20also%20constitutes%20a%20war%20crime%3F%20Also%20constitutes%20something%20that%20the%20ICC%20should%20investigate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EWithout%20a%20doubt%2C%20the%20current%20Israeli%20onslaught%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%20constitutes%20a%20war%20crime%2C%20and%20this%20is%20nothing%20new.%20The%20first%20Israeli%20attack%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%20was%20in%202008%20and%202009%2C%20and%20then%20there%20was%20the%20Goldstone%20Report%20%E2%80%93%20575%20pages%20%E2%80%93%20it%20deals%20with%2033%20episodes%2C%20and%20it%20details%20not%20one%2C%20not%20two%2C%20not%20three%2C%20but%20a%20whole%20series%20of%20Israeli%20war%20crimes%2C%20and%20Israel%20did%20not%20have%20to%20pay%20any%20price%20for%20committing%20those%20war%20crimes%20in%202008%20and%202009%2C%20or%20in%20any%20of%20the%20subsequent%20five%20attacks%20on%20Gaza.%20So%20Israel%20is%20a%20war%20criminal.%20Israel%20repeatedly%20commits%20war%20crimes%20in%20Gaza%20and%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20suffer%20any%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20My%20last%20question%20Professor%20Shlaim.%20How%20do%20people%20in%20Israel%2C%20your%20fellow%20citizens%2C%20regard%20your%20views%2C%20your%20thinking%2C%20and%20your%20comments%20on%20Israel%3F%20How%20do%20they%20respond%20when%20you%20say%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20what%20you%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%20has%20committed%20murder%20on%20a%20massive%20scale%20every%20day.%E2%80%9D%20You%20said%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%20was%20guilty%20of%20state%20terror%2C%E2%80%9D%20you%20said%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%20was%20guilty%20of%20war%20crimes%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20you%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Ca%20war%20criminal.%E2%80%9D%20How%20do%20your%20fellow%20Israelis%20respond%20to%20you%20when%20you%20speak%20in%20these%20terms%2C%20and%20when%20they%20hear%20your%20views%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIt%20depends%2C%20on%20which%20Israelis.%20Israelis%20on%20the%20left%20share%20my%20views.%20The%20majority%20of%20Israelis%2C%20who%20know%20about%20me%20%E2%80%93%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20that%20well%20known%20in%20Israel%20%E2%80%93%20would%20probably%20regard%20me%20as%20a%20traitor.%20But%20what%20is%20important%20to%20me%20is%20the%20truth.%20I%20am%20a%20historian%2C%20my%20main%20research%20interest%20is%20the%20Arab-Israeli%20conflict.%20So%20what%20I%20care%20about%20most%20is%20not%20what%20some%20Israelis%20think%20of%20me%2C%20but%20my%20duty%20as%20a%20public%20intellectual%2C%20and%20as%20a%20student%20of%20this%20conflict%2C%20to%20give%20the%20public%20%E2%80%93%20in%20my%20publications%2C%20in%20my%20books%2C%20in%20my%20articles%2C%20and%20in%20conversations%20with%20people%20like%20you%20%E2%80%93%20to%20give%20an%20account%20of%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20which%20is%20as%20truthful%20as%20possible%2C%20as%20honest%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20as%20fair-minded%20as%20possible.%20That%20is%20my%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20I%20thank%20you%20for%20giving%20me%20so%20much%20time%20to%20explain%20a%20very%20complicated%20and%20complex%20subject%20in%20ways%20that%20are%20simple%20and%20easy%20for%20an%20Indian%20audience%20to%20understand.%20People%20may%20not%20completely%20agree%20with%20your%20view%20and%20interpretation%20of%20Israel-Palestine%20history%2C%20but%20at%20least%20they%20will%20have%20heard%20from%20you%2C%20a%20view%20that%20they%20ought%20to%20pay%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20to%2C%20and%20a%20view%20which%20places%20what%20happened%20on%20October%207%20in%20a%20perspective%20that%20many%20in%20the%20media%20have%20not%20as%20yet%20conveyed.%20You%E2%80%99ve%20opened%20their%20eyes%2C%20now%20it%E2%80%99s%20for%20them%20to%20look%20out%20and%20see%20and%20believe.%20Thank%20you%20very%20much%20indeed%20for%20speaking%20to%20me.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThank%20you%20for%20giving%20me%20this%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranscribed%20by%20Uthara%20Vijay.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698486587000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28151151%2Fmaxresdefault.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffull-text-israel-palestine-karan-thapar-avi-shlaim%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Land%20grabbing%20and%20peacemaking%20don't%20go%20together%20and%20by%20constantly%20expanding%20settlements%2C%20Israel%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20prefers%20land%20to%20peace%2C%20professor%20Avi%20Shlaim%20told%20Karan%20Thapar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffull-text-israel-palestine-karan-thapar-avi-shlaim%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Will%20India%E2%80%99s%20Domestic%20Industrial%20Policy%20Help%20Integration%20With%20Global%20Value%20Chain%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28143150%2Fpexels-andrey-matveev-4211136.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIndustrial%20policy%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20government%20can%20play%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20building%20out%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%20for%20various%20purposes%2C%20is%20back%20globally.%20The%20United%20States%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20is%20the%20prime%20example%2C%20using%20state%20subsidies%2C%20tax%20breaks%2C%20loans%2C%20and%20grants%20to%20support%20industries%20that%20the%20US%20has%20deemed%20strategic.%20India%2C%20too%2C%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20this%20trend.%20India%20introduced%20Production%20Linked%20Incentives%20in%202020%2C%20providing%20a%20financial%20boost%20to%20firms%20that%20expanded%20their%20manufacturing%20within%20the%20country%2C%20starting%20with%20three%20industries%20%E2%80%93%20pharmaceutical%2C%20electronics%2C%20and%20medical%20devices%20%E2%80%93%20and%20then%20expanding%20them%20to%20cover%20many%20more%20sectors.%20%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20do%20these%20domestic-focused%20policies%20fit%20into%20broader%20efforts%20to%20integrate%20into%20the%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20value%20chain%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fpolitics%2Fminister-jaishankar-bats-for-re-globalisation-at-b20-summit-11693125052729.html%5C%22%3Ediversified%2C%20democratic%E2%80%9D%20re-globalisation%20that%20India%20has%20called%20for%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%2C%20we%20have%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20and%20the%20discourse%20around%20the%20global%20value%20chain%20that%20emerged%20at%20the%20time.%20The%20ripple%20effects%20of%20disruptions%20caused%20by%20the%20pandemic%20brought%20home%20the%20characteristics%20of%20a%20globalised%20world%20that%20obtains%20many%20items%20of%20consumption%20through%20the%20global%20value%20chain.%20The%20important%20question%20then%20turned%20to%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20these%20chains%20and%20their%20resilience.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20countries%20were%20trying%20to%20integrate%20into%20existing%20global%20value%20chains.%20Global%20value%20chain%20participation%20generally%20brings%20economic%20benefits%20in%20terms%20of%20enhanced%20productivity%20as%20well%20as%20greater%20sophistication%20and%20diversification%20of%20exports.%20Consequently%2C%20understanding%20what%20determines%20participation%20in%20global%20value%20chains%20has%20implications%20for%20policymaking.%20Yet%20the%20gains%20from%20value%20chain%20participation%20vary%20significantly%20between%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20integration%20in%20global%20value%20chains%20is%20captured%20through%20backward%20and%20forward%20linkages.%20Backward%20linkages%20measure%20how%20an%20economy%20imports%20intermediate%20goods%20or%20services%20as%20inputs%20in%20the%20production%20of%20its%20own%20exports%2C%20while%20forward%20linkages%20refer%20to%20inputs%20provided%20by%20one%20country%20to%20another%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20produces%20consumer%20goods%20that%20are%20further%20exported%20to%20third%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20times%2C%20many%20countries%20have%20resorted%20to%20industrial%20policy%20to%20decouple%20from%20over-reliance%20on%20certain%20trading%20partners.%20But%20how%20do%20we%20make%20sense%20of%20these%20production%20networks%20in%20the%20context%20of%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIntegration%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGlobal%20value%20chains%20are%20networked%20through%20lead%20firms%2C%20usually%20major%20multinational%20companies%20that%20play%20key%20roles%20in%20building%20these%20value%20chains.%20From%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%2C%20belonging%20to%20these%20chains%20leads%20to%20networks%20and%20exports.%20Global%20value%20chain%20participation%20is%20dependent%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20the%20size%20and%20location%20of%20a%20country%2C%20its%20manufacturing%20share%20in%20GDP%2C%20and%20trade%20and%20investment%20policies.%20A%20country%E2%80%99s%20global%20value%20chain%20integration%20matters%20due%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20trade%2C%20which%2C%20since%20the%20mid-1960s%2C%20has%20increasingly%20been%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS002219961100122X%5C%22%3Eintermediate%20goods%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20inputs%20that%20are%20used%20in%20the%20production%20process%20that%20lead%20to%20final%20consumer%20goods.%20Certain%20factors%20like%20lowering%20transport%20costs%2C%20easing%20tariffs%2C%20and%20technological%20advancements%20in%20transport%20have%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20trade%20in%20intermediates%20whereby%20value%20is%20added%20in%20each%20subsequent%20stage%20in%20factories%20located%20in%20different%20countries.%20This%20has%20led%20to%20regions%20or%20countries%20producing%20and%20specialising%20in%20certain%20goods%20and%20the%20moniker%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2Ftwec.12189%5C%22%3EFactory%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20for%20electronic%20products.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20not%20belonging%20to%20these%20chains%20means%20it%20is%20difficult%20for%20countries%20to%20break%20into%20export%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28143351%2FElectronics_factory_in_Shenzhen.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28143351%2FElectronics_factory_in_Shenzhen.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28143351%2FElectronics_factory_in_Shenzhen-300x165.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682243%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22562%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20an%20electronics%20factory%20in%20Shenzhen.%20Photo%3A%20Steve%20Jurvetson%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELead%20firms%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20these%2C%20the%20role%20of%20lead%20firms%20is%20important.%20Lead%20firms%20have%20been%20defined%20as%20small%2C%20medium%2C%20or%20large%20firms%20that%20have%20forward%20or%20backward%20linkages%20with%20a%20large%20number%20of%20micro%2C%20small%2C%20and%20medium%20enterprises%20(MSMEs).%20A%20lead%20firm%20governs%20the%20whole%20of%20a%20value%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20emergence%20of%20lead%20firms%20and%20global%20value%20chain%20participation%20depends%20on%20factors%20that%20lead%20to%20a%20conducive%20business%20environment%2C%20attracting%20foreign%20investment%2C%20and%20internationalisation%20of%20domestic%20firms.%20Internationalisation%20of%20domestic%20firms%20can%20be%20done%20when%20they%20start%20exporting%20to%20international%20buyers%20and%20through%20imports%20of%20intermediates%20by%20domestic%20final%20producers.%20Global%20value%20chains%20in%20manufacturing%20can%20better%20contribute%20to%20employment%20creation%2C%20skills%20upgrading%2C%20and%20other%20benefits%20associated%20with%20manufacturing-led%20industrialisation.%20Across%20this%20ecosystem%2C%20there%20is%20a%20desire%20to%20create%20an%20environment%20that%20supports%20local%20manufacturers%20as%20they%20attempt%20to%20upgrade%20their%20productive%20capabilities%20and%20increase%20their%20competitiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20domestic%20firms%20in%20developing%20countries%2C%20especially%20MSMEs%2C%20do%20not%20integrate%20into%20global%20value%20chains%20easily%2C%20and%20face%20challenges%20in%20global%20value%20chain%20participation.%20The%20rise%20in%20South-South%20trade%20has%20made%20local%20and%20regional%20value%20chains%20more%20important%20for%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20value%20chain%20literature%20stresses%20the%20role%20lead%20firms%20(such%20as%20global%20buyers)%20play%20in%20supporting%20producers%E2%80%99%20learning%20and%20innovation%20activities%20in%20less%20developed%20countries%20by%20transferring%20knowledge%20to%20their%20suppliers.%20However%2C%20it%20has%20been%20noted%20that%20while%20these%20firms%20generally%20outsource%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F42791981_A_Handbook_for_Value_Chain_Research%5C%22%3Ecommodity-like%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20activities%20that%20add%20little%20value%2C%20they%20retain%20direct%20control%20over%20intangible%2C%20high%20value-added%20activities%20as%20opposed%20to%20low%20value-added%20activities.%20Hence%2C%20the%20transfer%20of%20knowledge%20occurs%20more%20through%20certain%20activities%20or%20tasks%20and%20certain%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20upgrading%20to%20high%20value-added%20activities%20can%20raise%20domestic%20labour%20productivity%20and%20skills%2C%20developing%20countries%20are%20often%20locked%20in%20low%20value-added%20activities%20with%20little%20or%20no%20technology%20transfer.%20Upgrading%20is%20defined%20as%20%E2%80%9Cstrategies%20that%20firms%2C%20countries%2C%20or%20regions%20implement%20to%20move%20toward%20higher%20value-added%20activities%20and%20increased%20value%20capture.%E2%80%9D%20The%20role%20of%20leading%20firms%20becomes%20critical%20in%20this%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20policy%20perspective%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenknowledge.worldbank.org%2Fbitstreams%2F34999319-7d14-5033-8dd0-31225100cf68%2Fdownload%5C%22%3Ehow%20global%20value%20chains%20integrate%20into%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20critical%20and%20the%20role%20of%20the%20lead%20firm%20is%20vital.%20Also%2C%20the%20role%20of%20industrial%20and%20other%20policies%20in%20encouraging%20global%20value%20chain%20integration%20and%20upgrading%20is%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhither%20industrial%20policy%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndustrial%20policy%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20development%20policy%20and%20has%20often%20taken%20various%20names%20(e.g.%2C%20export%20facilitation%2C%20promotion%20of%20foreign%20investment%2C%20or%20free%20trade%20zones).%20It%20is%20not%20only%20about%20incentives%20given%20to%20manufacturing%20industries%20but%20also%20those%20given%20to%20services%20or%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETheoretically%2C%20the%20argument%20for%20industrial%20policy%20stems%20from%20market%20failure.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrodrik.scholar.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Fdani-rodrik%2Ffiles%2Fgreen_industrial_policy.pdf%5C%22%3EEconomist%20Dani%20Rodrik%20argues%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20need%20for%20industrial%20policy%20is%20theoretically%20sound%20and%20well-articulated.%20It%20can%20address%20market%20failures%2C%20but%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20implement%20in%20practice.%20As%20he%20explains%2C%20the%20conventional%20case%20for%20industrial%20policy%20is%20due%20to%20market%20failures%20in%20markets%20for%20credit%2C%20labour%2C%20products%2C%20or%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20main%20objections%20to%20industrial%20policy%20in%20practice%2C%20according%20to%20Rodrik.%20One%20is%20information%20asymmetry%20and%20the%20other%20is%20corruption%20and%20rent-seeking.%20In%20the%20first%20case%2C%20it%20is%20impossible%20for%20governments%20to%20identify%20winners%20in%20firms%2C%20sectors%2C%20or%20markets%20that%20are%20impacted%20by%20imperfect%20markets%20%E2%80%93%20yet%20industrial%20policy%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20forces%20them%20to.%20Secondly%2C%20it%20is%20argued%20that%20industrial%20policy%20often%20leads%20to%20corruption%20or%20rent-seeking.%20There%20are%20arguments%20on%20the%20empirical%20evaluation%20of%20industrial%20policy%20by%20both%20the%20proponents%20and%20opponents%20of%20industrial%20policy.%20Proponents%20suggest%20that%20in%20many%20instances%2C%20usually%20backed%20by%20case-based%20evidence%2C%20industrial%20policy%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20integration%20and%20industrial%20policy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20India%E2%80%99s%20manufacturing%20prowess%2C%20especially%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F09692290.2012.756414%5C%22%3Emedium-tech%20industries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20participation%20in%20global%20value%20chains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FGlobal-Value-Chains-and-the-Missing-Links-Cases-from-Indian-Industry%2FRay-Miglani%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780367734503%5C%22%3Eremains%20limited%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Moreover%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20global%20value%20chains%20is%20largely%20concentrated%20in%20a%20few%20industries%20(e.g.%20automobiles).%20India%20has%20also%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F00157325211073848%5C%22%3Elosing%20its%20share%20of%20exports%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20labour-intensive%20products%2C%20especially%20garments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20India%2C%20while%20product%20upgrading%20(defined%20as%20the%20movement%20into%20higher%20value-added%20products%20within%20a%20global%20value%20chain)%20and%20process%20upgrading%20(which%20involves%20increased%20productivity%20in%20existing%20activities%20within%20a%20global%20value%20chain)%20have%20occurred%2C%20functional%20upgrading%20(which%20involves%20the%20movement%20into%20more%20technologically%20sophisticated%20or%20more%20integrated%20aspects%20of%20a%20production%20process)%20and%20intersectoral%20upgrading%20has%20been%20limited.%20This%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adb.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublication%2F183908%2Fsawp-043.pdf%5C%22%3Ebeen%20the%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20garments.%20Inter-sectoral%20or%20chain%20upgrading%20involves%20a%20move%20into%20higher%20value-added%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20countries%20can%20better%20stimulate%20their%20integration%20into%20global%20value%20chains%20and%20increase%20the%20development%20benefits%20from%20multi-national%20company%20activities%20in%20their%20economies%20by%20aligning%20their%20policies%20to%20attract%20Foreign%20Direct%20Investment.%20The%20typology%20of%20industrial%20policies%20that%20countries%20can%20follow%20in%20enhancing%20global%20value%20chain%20participation%20includes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F281901582_Global_Value_Chain-Oriented_Industrial_Policy_The_Role_of_Emerging_Economies%5C%22%3Ethree%20sets%20of%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficrier.org%2Fpdf%2FWorking_Paper_386.pdf%5C%22%3Ehorizontal%3C%2Fa%3E%20policies%20that%20affect%20the%20entire%20national%20economy%20(e.g.%20the%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax)%2C%20vertical%20industrial%20policies%20that%20are%20targeted%20at%20particular%20sectors%20or%20industries%20(e.g.%20Automotive%20Mission%20Plan%202016-26%20for%20the%20automobile%20industry)%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20global%20value%20chain-oriented%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20last%20type%20of%20policy%20could%20include%20the%20possibility%20of%20upgrading%20and%20improving%20the%20links%20across%20different%20segments%20of%20the%20value%20chain.%20India%E2%80%99s%20policy%20approach%20has%20been%20largely%20addressing%20logistical%20and%20infrastructure%20bottlenecks%20and%20improving%20the%20ease%20of%20doing%20business%2C%20and%20can%20be%20classified%20in%20terms%20of%20horizontal%20or%20vertical.%20However%2C%20what%20is%20needed%20for%20greater%20integration%20is%20global%20value%20chain-oriented%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndustrial%20policy%202.0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20times%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20resurgence%20of%20industrial%20policy%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%2C%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%2C%20the%20recent%20production-linked%20incentive%20(PLI)%20schemes.%20These%20policies%20have%20been%20announced%20for%20fourteen%20sectors%20and%20could%20be%20extended%20to%20more%20in%20the%20future.%20They%20are%20India%E2%80%99s%20newest%20set%20of%20industrial%20policies%20after%20the%20earlier%20%E2%80%9CMake%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20programme.%20Through%20these%20schemes%2C%20India%20is%20trying%20to%20attract%20FDI%20and%20create%20%E2%80%9Cchampion%20firms.%E2%80%9D%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Foreign%20Trade%20Policy%20announced%20earlier%20this%20year%20has%20the%20objective%20of%20integrating%20India%20into%20global%20value%20chains%20and%20making%20India%20an%20export%20hub.%20It%20is%20in%20this%20context%20that%20we%20need%20to%20see%20the%20PLI%20schemes%20aimed%20at%20improving%20the%20international%20competitiveness%20of%20the%20firms%20and%20increasing%20the%20localisation%20of%20Indian%20industries.%20The%20PLI%20schemes%20should%20also%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20context%20of%20global%20value%20chain-oriented%20policies%20aimed%20at%20increasing%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20value%20chain%20integration.%20By%20trying%20to%20create%20champion%20firms%2C%20these%20policies%20are%20trying%20to%20pick%20%E2%80%9Cwinners%E2%80%9D%20which%20is%20in%20line%20with%20the%20objectives%20of%20industrial%20policy.%20However%2C%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20whether%20these%20firms%20will%20also%20become%20lead%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20line%20with%20the%20policy%20announcements%2C%20the%20tariffs%20on%20imported%20inputs%20have%20been%20increased%20to%20promote%20indigenous%20manufacturing.%20While%20these%20may%20work%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20in%20sectors%20where%20there%20is%20no%20capacity%20(e.g.%20solar%20panels%2C%20EV%20batteries)%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20production%20increases%20in%20the%20short%20run.%20What%20India%20is%20trying%E2%80%94through%20a%20combination%20of%20PLI%20schemes%20and%20import%20tariffs%20%E2%80%93%20is%20to%20create%20a%20larger%20part%20of%20the%20production%20chain%20within%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20successful%2C%20India%20will%20have%20built%20a%20successful%20indigenous%20manufacturing%20base%20capable%20of%20exporting%2C%20too.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20the%20manufacturing%20of%20the%20inputs%20does%20not%20become%20globally%20competitive%20despite%20the%20tariff%20protection%2C%20India%20will%20have%20lost%20the%20chance%20to%20integrate%20even%20the%20downstream%20industry%20into%20the%20value%20chains%20of%20%E2%80%9CFactory%20Asia.%E2%80%9D%20The%20distinction%20between%20industrial%20policy%20and%20import%20substitution%20needs%20to%20be%20understood.%20Import%20substitution%20can%20lead%20to%20greater%20reliance%20on%20domestically%20produced%20intermediates%20%E2%80%93%20thereby%20promoting%20indigenous%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%93%20but%20need%20not%20lead%20to%20greater%20global%20value%20chain%20integration.%20Hence%2C%20the%20objective%20of%20greater%20integration%20with%20global%20value%20chains%20through%20the%20PLI%20schemes%20is%20uncertain.%20Whether%20these%20policies%20will%20propel%20India%E2%80%99s%20manufacturing%20sector%20and%20help%20overcome%20the%20%E2%80%9Cjobless%20growth%E2%80%9D%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ESaon%20Ray%20is%20an%20author%20and%20economist%20specialising%20in%20industry%20and%20international%20trade.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20in%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Famritajash%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Fudayandas%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1697624538309000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1hHpUZI4jlNYa6b8cG0NpI%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Fudayandas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%20in%20Transition%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20publication%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India%20(University%20of%20Pennsylvania).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698484206000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28143150%2Fpexels-andrey-matveev-4211136.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findia-domestic-industrial-policy-global-value-chain%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20is%20among%20the%20countries%20that%20have%20used%20industrial%20policy%20to%20decouple%20from%20over-reliance%20on%20certain%20trading%20partners%20in%20recent%20times.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findia-domestic-industrial-policy-global-value-chain%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Crash%20involving%20passenger%20bus%20in%20Egypt%20kills%2032%20and%20injures%2060%22%